body: New version of 3rd party libraries -> increasing min requirements

Hi all, long time no see! I have merged all changed from the current Porchetta repo to github, fulfilling the original promise that the code we're producing on Porchetta will be always made public over time.
(pls support us regardless)

Introducing better exceptions.
New API: sid_for_dn
Some minor fixes in the new features.
Adding rate limiting option for paged queries. This functionality can be set up from cmdline parameters as well!
Added the option to drop back to interactive shell using the 'i' command in the sample client

New features:
 - Get and set SecurityDescriptors of arbitrary DNs
 - List all computer dns names
 - New client function: computer (gets computer information based on samaccoutname)

Fixes:
 - LAPS password read now actually returns the passwords
 - User creation stability improved
 - modify function now doesn't crash with empty control variable input
